  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Civic Participation and Social Accountability in the Fight Against Judicial Corruption</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activity 1: Create citizens awareness on civic participation in the Judiciary. 

Activity 2: Develop materials for Court Users. 

Activity 3: Organise Education Programs for Court Users

Activity 4: Create an SMS/ Hotline for Citizens Complaints on Judicial Corruption.

Activity 5: Create and Train Civic Monitoring Teams

Activity 6: Undertake Citizens monitoring activities.

Activity 7: Organise Participatory District Review Meetings

Activity 8: Undertake Civic Actions on Judicial Performance 

Activity 9: Promote Police Actions</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Result 1: Institutionalized interface platforms for citizens engagement with the judiciary

Result 2: Increased demand public accountability in the judiciary;

Result 4: Improved judicial openness and accountability to citizens and corruption

Result 5: Reduction in court delays in justice delivery response</narrative>
  </description>
